issue.title: Crash detection
issue.body: interesting app. How is your crash detection? Did you test it if it works? Looks like even with a hard brake, it will show as accident.

comment.body:
1) yes the acceleration includes gravity! It is taking the magnitude in XYZ and comparing it with the previous value so the gravity is always accounted for as a constant. If it goes below the threshold (which you can tune), it triggers the alarm. We are assuming the user is driving and a crash is detected when there is sudden deceleration. 

2) the values are being pulled by "onSensorChange" which gets callback every time the sensor gets a new value. I believe this depends on the sensor on your phone. From what I've seen, it looks like 100Hz on my phone (Samsung S7 Edge).

Hope this helps!
